	  <title>Linear Equations with Exactly One Solutions</title>
	  <caption>Linear Equations with Exactly One Solutions</caption>
	  <showme>
		    <statement.showme>
			      <para>
            <para.body>If a system of linear equations exactly one solution, then the solution hyperplanes of its equations have exactly one point in common.</para.body>
         </para>
			
			      <para align="center">
            <para.body>
               <media type="image" active="0" inline="0">
                  <img src="ims/ThreeEqnsR3Generic.gif"/>
               </media>
            </para.body>
         </para>
			
			      <para>
            <para.body>The RREF of a system of linear equations indicates that the system has exactly one solution as follows: There is no leading <math>
                  <latex>1</latex>
               </math> in the augmented part of the RREF, and each column of its non-augmented part contains a leading <math>
                  <latex>1</latex>
               </math>.</para.body>
         </para>
			
			      <math.display>
				        <latex>
					
\begin{array}{cccccc|c}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; d_1 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; d_2 \\
\vdots &amp; \vdots &amp; \vdots &amp;\ddots &amp;        &amp; \vdots &amp; \vdots \\
\vdots &amp; \vdots &amp; \vdots &amp;       &amp; \ddots &amp; \vdots &amp; \vdots \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; \cdots &amp; 1 &amp; d_r \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
\vdots &amp; \vdots &amp; \vdots &amp; &amp; &amp; \vdots  &amp; \vdots \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
\end{array}
					
				</latex>
			      </math.display>
			
			      <para>
            <para.body>Indeed, the <math>
                  <latex>j</latex>
               </math>-th row of this reduced augmented coefficient matrix corresponds to the equation</para.body>
         </para>
			
			      <math.display>
				        <latex>x_j = t_j\qquad 1\leq j\leq n</latex>
			      </math.display>
			
			      <para>
            <para.body>So the only solution of the given system is the vector</para.body>
         </para>
			
			      <math.display>
				        <latex>(d_1,d_2,\dots,d_r)</latex>
			      </math.display>
		    </statement.showme>
